				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/voct" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(392303); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=392303&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182937" alt="Voct" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=392303)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/voct" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(392303); return false;" >Voct</a></span> <span class="odate time_1289758371 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 Nov 2010 18:12</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-924855">
									

<p>I had a talk with Erk about this on IRC;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">here's&nbsp;the&nbsp;log</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">bleh</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>&lt;Voct&gt; Erk - you saw my post on the discussion for that RadioKinetic Anomaly ?<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; the newer one voct?<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; yeah<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; Raccoons.<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; picture it<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; a room full of angry caged raccoons<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; all of them talking<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; saying random stuff that they've pulled out of radio communications<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; hahaha<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Do they have a speaker-crackle voice, or a strange squeaky racoon voice?<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Like, do they act like speakers for the signal<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; a combination of (the voice of the person who originally spoke it) and (the raccoon growl)<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; That would certainly give the scp a bit more pizzazz<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; oh, and because it affects all raccoons *in the vicinity*<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; once you capture all the raccoons in a given area<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; more will move in<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; so the Foundation has to send people out every night<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; to hunt down all the raccoons in the area<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Hahaha<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; and check<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; to see if they speak English.<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Do they remain affected if they leave?<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; I think raccoons that get affected should remain radio receivers<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; maybe less powerful, but they'll still wander around quoting cell phone communications and things<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; At the epicenter they're far more potent though.<br />
&lt;Aelanna&gt; &#8230; radio racoons?<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; yeah<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; yeah<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; aelanna, we're figuring how to make !scp-724 actually interesting<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; raccoons that leave the radius of effect will only quote cellphone stuff if they're way close to a transmitter or something?<br />
&lt;Aelanna&gt; I saw that last night<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; hm<br />
&lt;Aelanna&gt; Lei is the original author?<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; Yeah<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; hm<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; maybe they remain receivers, but not speakers?<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; how do you mean? If they don't speak anymore it wouldn't be clear they were receiving would it?<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; Erk - they get all upset if you broadcast static<br />
&lt;cbc&gt; well hey maybe they'll respond and let me do this tongiht?<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; dunno<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Personally I think it'd be more fun if they just randomly started speaking on occasion.<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Much more rarely though<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; Erk - it's just stuff they intercept from the radio communication<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; but you're walking outside, taking out the garbage, when suddenly you catch sight of a raccoon in a nearby tree. You make eye contact, and the raccoon stares back. Then it says &quot;Fourteen soldiers were injured today in a suicide bombing.&quot;<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; Erk - that's a wonderful image.<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; Erk - I'm thinking of it being called &quot;Radio Receiver Raccoons&quot; ?<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Voct, I'd say either Radio Raccoons or Receiver Raccoons would be punchier&#8230;<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; okay<br />
&lt;Hungry_Man&gt; Radio Raccoons, definitely.<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; The raccoon crews could disguise themselves as homeless people<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; or total rednecks depending on the environment<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; neither homeless nor rednecks would have tranq darts<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; I do wonder if they'd be tranquing the raccoons at this stage&#8230; wouldn't they have enough?<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Oooh<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; unless each raccoon was 'tuned' to a certain frequency when it was exposed to the SCP<br />
&lt;Doc_Kens&gt; Why does this remind me of a Studio Ghibli film?<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; Erk - we don't know. So we keep them.<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; Just in case.<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; so the storage facility consists of rows upon rows of cages labelled with frequencies, each cage containing a raccoon<br />
Voct&gt; a VERY ANGRY raccoon<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; quoting someone's cell conversation<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; don't you love it?<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; &quot;Snarl, hiss. Never call me anymore, why is that. Grrrr. Did the shopping for you yesterday. SPit spit&quot;<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Or, rather than frequency<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; and then just as the raccoon starts to say something interesting and useful&#8230;<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; it stops talking and starts eating.<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Each raccoon locks onto a specific signal, changing even when that signal is modulated<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; so, like, if it starts picking up the radio transmissions of an al qaeda cell in afghanistan, it will always pick up that cell's transmissions even if they change walkie talkies<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; which is useless unless you have someone who recognizes Pashto<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; and it's all linked back to the nearby confluence of towers<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Yep. And even then he translates it as &quot;Growl growl, Ahid went to the village and brought back some bread. Snarl. Yeah, I love that bakery too.&quot; and then the coon takes a drink.<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Leading to a massive issue with data sifting<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; Erk - the worst part would be when two raccoons are spouting different sides of the same conversation<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; hah they probably have a few where they've realised they're tuned to people who often talk to each other.<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; so they keep the cages side-by-side<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; and then the raccoons start trying to attack each other through their cages<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; all the while talking romantically to each other<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; I can see the guards now. &quot;Hey, Jim, 0449 and 0450 are fighting again. Want to take bets?&quot; &quot;Oh, sorry Sam, I heard them earlier today. 0449 forgot to pick the kids up from school.&quot;<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; &quot;Hey sweety, how was SNARL SNARL GROWL BITE CAGE&quot;, &quot;Oh, it was great, I got a RATTLE GROWL SPIT&quot;<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; &quot;Note: yes, the conversations between SCP-724-056 and SCP-724-058 are adorable. But 056 and 058 hate each other and have injured themselves trying to claw their way through the cages.&quot;<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; For the sake of humour, SCP infection should make the raccoons more ornery<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; well<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; we're not sure if it's because of the infection<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; or because, y'know<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; they've been captured and are being kept in small cages<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; not *too* small<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; we don't want to risk damaging their health<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Actually to be a little more scp'ish, maybe receiving radio transmissions is uncomfortable to them as well<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; mildly activating pain centers in the brain consistent with a constant itching sensation<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; Erk - then raccoons wouldn't be constantly entering the territory<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; they wouldn't feel the itch until they'd been infected, though<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; I still don't like it<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; Fair enough.<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; It's also possible that they are constantly itchy, but emitting the radio signals reduces the feeling<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; hmm<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; so infected raccoons tend to return to the area if they are clever enough to make the connection, because it's easier to broadcast there<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; I gotta go though, battery is dead and no plugin<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; ttyl<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; good luck with the crazy coons<br />
&lt;Erk&gt; [having a reason for them to return to the area might be a good plan, because otherwise it's hard to imagine the Foundation being able to keep this one secret]<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; crazy white-trash rednecks babbling about talking raccoons?<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; I think it should just be a reasonably good territory for raccoons to live in<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; no itch, no pain<br />
&lt;Voct&gt; just yummy garbage, safe attics, and the goddamn Foundation shooting them with tranq darts and sticking them in cages.</p>
</div>
