<p>I'll try a rewrite based on that idea, since it does sound cool. Not sure I want to have a wide area-of-effect (since that would be sufficiently obnoxious to contain that the Foundation would have just as likely had one of the radio towers shut down), but there are almost certainly some raccoons still out there that were affected before the Foundation moved in and put a building on top of the anomaly. Perhaps even include a suggestion that the effect includes genetic/epigenetic alterations, so that affected specimens can potentially pass it on to their offspring?</p>
